{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk about 4.6 billion years of history"},{"time":5000,"text":"in 18 minutes."},{"time":7000,"text":"That's 300 million years per minute."},{"time":10000,"text":"Let's start with the first photograph NASA obtained"},{"time":14000,"text":"of planet Mars."},{"time":16000,"text":"This is fly-by, Mariner IV."},{"time":18000,"text":"It was taken in 1965."},{"time":21000,"text":"When this picture appeared,"},{"time":23000,"text":"that well-known scientific journal,"},{"time":26000,"text":"The New York Times, wrote in its editorial,"},{"time":29000,"text":"\"Mars is uninteresting."},{"time":31000,"text":"It's a dead world. NASA should not spend"},{"time":34000,"text":"any time or effort studying Mars anymore.\""},{"time":38000,"text":"Fortunately, our leaders in Washington"},{"time":40000,"text":"at NASA headquarters knew better"},{"time":42000,"text":"and we began a very extensive study"},{"time":46000,"text":"of the red planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"One of the key questions in all of science,"},{"time":52000,"text":"\"Is there life outside of Earth?\""},{"time":54000,"text":"I believe that Mars is the most likely target"},{"time":58000,"text":"for life outside the Earth."},{"time":60000,"text":"I'm going to show you in a few minutes"},{"time":62000,"text":"some amazing measurements that suggest"},{"time":64000,"text":"there may be life on Mars."},{"time":66000,"text":"But let me start with a Viking photograph."},{"time":70000,"text":"This is a composite taken by Viking in 1976."},{"time":74000,"text":"Viking was developed and managed at the"},{"time":77000,"text":"NASA Langley Research Center."},{"time":79000,"text":"We sent two orbiters and two landers in the summer of 1976."},{"time":83000,"text":"We had four spacecraft, two around Mars,"},{"time":87000,"text":"two on the surface --"},{"time":89000,"text":"an amazing accomplishment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"This is the first photograph taken from"},{"time":93000,"text":"the surface of any planet."},{"time":95000,"text":"This is a Viking Lander photograph"},{"time":97000,"text":"of the surface of Mars."},{"time":99000,"text":"And yes, the red planet is red."},{"time":102000,"text":"Mars is half the size of the Earth,"},{"time":105000,"text":"but because two-thirds of the Earth is covered by water,"},{"time":108000,"text":"the land area on Mars"},{"time":111000,"text":"is comparable to the land area on Earth."},{"time":113000,"text":"So, Mars is a pretty big place even though it's half the size."},{"time":118000,"text":"We have obtained topographic measurements"},{"time":121000,"text":"of the surface of Mars. We understand"},{"time":123000,"text":"the elevation differences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"We know a lot about Mars."},{"time":127000,"text":"Mars has the largest volcano in the solar system,"},{"time":131000,"text":"Olympus Mons."},{"time":133000,"text":"Mars has the Grand Canyon"},{"time":135000,"text":"of the solar system, Valles Marineris."},{"time":138000,"text":"Very, very interesting planet."},{"time":140000,"text":"Mars has the largest"},{"time":143000,"text":"impact crater in the solar system,"},{"time":145000,"text":"Hellas Basin."},{"time":147000,"text":"This is 2,000 miles across."},{"time":149000,"text":"If you happened to be on Mars"},{"time":151000,"text":"when this impactor hit,"},{"time":153000,"text":"it was a really bad day on Mars."},{"time":155000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":157000,"text":"This is Olympus Mons."},{"time":159000,"text":"This is bigger than the state of Arizona."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"Volcanoes are important, because volcanoes"},{"time":164000,"text":"produce atmospheres and they produce oceans."},{"time":167000,"text":"We're looking at Valles Marineris,"},{"time":170000,"text":"the largest canyon in the solar system,"},{"time":172000,"text":"superimposed on a map of the United States,"},{"time":175000,"text":"3,000 miles across."},{"time":177000,"text":"One of the most intriguing features about Mars,"},{"time":180000,"text":"the National Academy of Science says"},{"time":182000,"text":"one of the 10 major mysteries of the space age,"},{"time":185000,"text":"is why certain areas of Mars"},{"time":188000,"text":"are so highly magnetized."},{"time":190000,"text":"We call this crustal magnetism."},{"time":192000,"text":"There are regions on Mars, where, for some reason --"},{"time":195000,"text":"we don't understand why at this point --"},{"time":198000,"text":"the surface is very, very highly magnetized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"Is there water on Mars?"},{"time":203000,"text":"The answer is no, there is no liquid water"},{"time":206000,"text":"on the surface of Mars today."},{"time":208000,"text":"But there is intriguing evidence"},{"time":210000,"text":"that suggests that the early history of Mars"},{"time":213000,"text":"there may have been rivers"},{"time":215000,"text":"and fast flowing water."},{"time":218000,"text":"Today Mars is very very dry."},{"time":220000,"text":"We believe there's some water in the polar caps,"},{"time":223000,"text":"there are polar caps of North Pole and South Pole."},{"time":226000,"text":"Here are some recent images."},{"time":228000,"text":"This is from Spirit and Opportunity."},{"time":231000,"text":"These images that show at one time,"},{"time":233000,"text":"there was very fast flowing water on the surface of Mars."},{"time":237000,"text":"Why is water important? Water is important"},{"time":239000,"text":"because if you want life you have to have water."},{"time":243000,"text":"Water is the key ingredient"},{"time":245000,"text":"in the evolution, the origin of life on a planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"Here is some picture of Antarctica"},{"time":251000,"text":"and a picture of Olympus Mons,"},{"time":254000,"text":"very similar features, glaciers."},{"time":256000,"text":"So, this is frozen water."},{"time":258000,"text":"This is ice water on Mars."},{"time":261000,"text":"This is my favorite picture. This was just taken a few weeks ago."},{"time":264000,"text":"It has not been seen publicly."},{"time":266000,"text":"This is European space agency"},{"time":269000,"text":"Mars Express, image of a crater on Mars"},{"time":271000,"text":"and in the middle of the crater"},{"time":273000,"text":"we have liquid water, we have ice."},{"time":276000,"text":"Very intriguing photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"We now believe that in the early history of Mars,"},{"time":282000,"text":"which is 4.6 billion years ago,"},{"time":285000,"text":"4.6 billion years ago, Mars was very Earth-like."},{"time":289000,"text":"Mars had rivers, Mars had lakes,"},{"time":292000,"text":"but more important Mars had planetary-scale oceans."},{"time":296000,"text":"We believe that the oceans were in the northern hemisphere,"},{"time":300000,"text":"and this area in blue,"},{"time":302000,"text":"which shows a depression of about four miles,"},{"time":305000,"text":"was the ancient ocean area"},{"time":308000,"text":"on the surface of Mars."},{"time":310000,"text":"Where did the ocean's worth of water on Mars go?"},{"time":313000,"text":"Well, we have an idea."},{"time":315000,"text":"This is a measurement we obtained a few years ago"},{"time":318000,"text":"from a Mars-orbiting satellite called Odyssey."},{"time":322000,"text":"Sub-surface water on Mars,"},{"time":324000,"text":"frozen in the form of ice."},{"time":327000,"text":"And this shows the percent. If it's a blueish color,"},{"time":330000,"text":"it means 16 percent by weight."},{"time":333000,"text":"Sixteen percent, by weight, of the interior"},{"time":335000,"text":"contains frozen water, or ice."},{"time":338000,"text":"So, there is a lot of water below the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"The most intriguing and puzzling measurement,"},{"time":345000,"text":"in my opinion, we've obtained of Mars,"},{"time":348000,"text":"was released earlier this year"},{"time":351000,"text":"in the magazine Science."},{"time":354000,"text":"And what we're looking at is the presence of the gas methane,"},{"time":358000,"text":"CH4, in the atmosphere of Mars."},{"time":362000,"text":"And you can see there are three distinct regions of methane."},{"time":366000,"text":"Why is methane important?"},{"time":368000,"text":"Because on Earth, almost all --"},{"time":370000,"text":"99.9 percent -- of the methane"},{"time":373000,"text":"is produced by living systems,"},{"time":376000,"text":"not little green men, but microscopic life"},{"time":380000,"text":"below the surface or at the surface."},{"time":382000,"text":"We now have evidence"},{"time":384000,"text":"that methane is in the atmosphere of Mars,"},{"time":387000,"text":"a gas that, on Earth,"},{"time":389000,"text":"is biogenic in origin,"},{"time":391000,"text":"produced by living systems."},{"time":393000,"text":"These are the three plumes: A, B1, B2."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"And this is the terrain it appears over,"},{"time":400000,"text":"and we know from geological studies"},{"time":403000,"text":"that these regions are the oldest regions on Mars."},{"time":407000,"text":"In fact, the Earth and Mars"},{"time":409000,"text":"are both 4.6 billion years old."},{"time":413000,"text":"The oldest rock on Earth is only 3.6 billion."},{"time":417000,"text":"The reason there is a billion-year gap"},{"time":420000,"text":"in our geological understanding"},{"time":422000,"text":"is because of plate tectonics,"},{"time":424000,"text":"The crust of the Earth has been recycled."},{"time":427000,"text":"We have no geological record prior"},{"time":429000,"text":"for the first billion years."},{"time":431000,"text":"That record exists on Mars."},{"time":433000,"text":"And this terrain that we're looking at"},{"time":435000,"text":"dates back to 4.6 billion years"},{"time":439000,"text":"when Earth and Mars were formed."},{"time":442000,"text":"It was a Tuesday."},{"time":444000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"This is a map that shows"},{"time":448000,"text":"where we've put our spacecraft on the surface of Mars."},{"time":452000,"text":"Here is Viking I, Viking II."},{"time":455000,"text":"This is Opportunity. This is Spirit."},{"time":458000,"text":"This is Mars Pathfinder. This is Phoenix,"},{"time":460000,"text":"we just put two years ago."},{"time":462000,"text":"Notice all of our rovers and all of our landers"},{"time":466000,"text":"have gone to the northern hemisphere."},{"time":468000,"text":"That's because the northern hemisphere"},{"time":471000,"text":"is the region of the ancient"},{"time":473000,"text":"ocean basin."},{"time":475000,"text":"There aren't many craters."},{"time":477000,"text":"And that's because the water protected the basin"},{"time":480000,"text":"from being impacted by asteroids and meteorites."},{"time":484000,"text":"But look in the southern hemisphere."},{"time":487000,"text":"In the southern hemisphere there are impact craters,"},{"time":489000,"text":"there are volcanic craters."},{"time":491000,"text":"Here's Hellas Basin,"},{"time":493000,"text":"a very very different place, geologically."},{"time":496000,"text":"Look where the methane is, the methane is in a very"},{"time":499000,"text":"rough terrain area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503000,"text":"What is the best way to unravel"},{"time":505000,"text":"the mysteries on Mars that exist?"},{"time":508000,"text":"We asked this question 10 years ago."},{"time":512000,"text":"We invited 10 of the top Mars scientists"},{"time":515000,"text":"to the Langley Research Center for two days."},{"time":519000,"text":"We addressed on the board"},{"time":521000,"text":"the major questions that have not been answered."},{"time":524000,"text":"And we spent two days deciding"},{"time":527000,"text":"how to best answer this question."},{"time":530000,"text":"And the result of our meeting"},{"time":533000,"text":"was a robotic rocket-powered airplane we call ARES."},{"time":539000,"text":"It's an Aerial Regional-scale Environmental Surveyor."},{"time":543000,"text":"There's a model of ARES here."},{"time":545000,"text":"This is a 20-percent scale model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"This airplane was designed at the Langley Research Center."},{"time":552000,"text":"If any place in the world"},{"time":554000,"text":"can build an airplane to fly on Mars,"},{"time":556000,"text":"it's the Langley Research Center,"},{"time":558000,"text":"for almost 100 years"},{"time":560000,"text":"a leading center of aeronautics in the world."},{"time":563000,"text":"We fly about a mile above the surface."},{"time":566000,"text":"We cover hundreds of miles,"},{"time":568000,"text":"and we fly about 450 miles an hour."},{"time":571000,"text":"We can do things that rovers can't do"},{"time":574000,"text":"and landers can't do:"},{"time":576000,"text":"We can fly above mountains, volcanoes, impact craters;"},{"time":579000,"text":"we fly over valleys;"},{"time":581000,"text":"we can fly over surface magnetism,"},{"time":583000,"text":"the polar caps, subsurface water;"},{"time":586000,"text":"and we can search for life on Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"But, of equal importance,"},{"time":590000,"text":"as we fly through the atmosphere of Mars,"},{"time":593000,"text":"we transmit that journey,"},{"time":596000,"text":"the first flight of an airplane outside of the Earth,"},{"time":599000,"text":"we transmit those images back to Earth."},{"time":602000,"text":"And our goal is to inspire the American public"},{"time":606000,"text":"who is paying for this mission through tax dollars."},{"time":609000,"text":"But more important we will"},{"time":612000,"text":"inspire the next generation of scientists,"},{"time":615000,"text":"technologists, engineers and mathematicians."},{"time":618000,"text":"And that's a critical area of national security"},{"time":622000,"text":"and economic vitality, to make sure"},{"time":626000,"text":"we produce the next generation"},{"time":628000,"text":"of scientists, engineers, mathematicians and technologists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"This is what ARES looks like"},{"time":634000,"text":"as it flies over Mars."},{"time":636000,"text":"We preprogram it."},{"time":638000,"text":"We will fly where the methane is."},{"time":640000,"text":"We will have instruments aboard the plane"},{"time":643000,"text":"that will sample, every three minutes, the atmosphere of Mars."},{"time":646000,"text":"We will look for methane"},{"time":648000,"text":"as well as other gasses"},{"time":650000,"text":"produced by living systems."},{"time":652000,"text":"We will pinpoint where these gases emanate from,"},{"time":656000,"text":"because we can measure the gradient where it comes from,"},{"time":659000,"text":"and there, we can direct the next mission"},{"time":662000,"text":"to land right in that area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"How do we transport an airplane to Mars?"},{"time":668000,"text":"In two words, very carefully."},{"time":671000,"text":"The problem is we don't fly it to Mars,"},{"time":675000,"text":"we put it in a spacecraft"},{"time":678000,"text":"and we send it to Mars."},{"time":680000,"text":"The problem is the spacecraft's"},{"time":682000,"text":"largest diameter is nine feet;"},{"time":686000,"text":"ARES is 21-foot wingspan, 17 feet long."},{"time":691000,"text":"How do we get it to Mars?"},{"time":693000,"text":"We fold it,"},{"time":695000,"text":"and we transport it in a spacecraft."},{"time":698000,"text":"And we have it in something called an aeroshell."},{"time":701000,"text":"This is how we do it."},{"time":703000,"text":"And we have a little video that describes the sequence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"Video: Seven, six. Green board. Five, four, three, two, one."},{"time":712000,"text":"Main engine start, and liftoff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Joel Levine: This is a launch from the Kennedy Space Center in Florida."},{"time":734000,"text":"This is the spacecraft taking nine months"},{"time":736000,"text":"to get to Mars."},{"time":738000,"text":"It enters the atmosphere of Mars."},{"time":741000,"text":"A lot of heating,"},{"time":746000,"text":"frictional heating. It's going 18 thousand miles an hour."},{"time":748000,"text":"A parachute opens up to slow it down."},{"time":752000,"text":"The thermal tiles fall off."},{"time":755000,"text":"The airplane is exposed to the atmosphere for the first time."},{"time":758000,"text":"It unfolds."},{"time":761000,"text":"The rocket engine begins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"We believe that in a one-hour flight"},{"time":773000,"text":"we can rewrite the textbook on Mars"},{"time":776000,"text":"by making high-resolution measurements of the atmosphere,"},{"time":779000,"text":"looking for gases of biogenic origin,"},{"time":782000,"text":"looking for gases of volcanic origin,"},{"time":785000,"text":"studying the surface, studying the magnetism"},{"time":788000,"text":"on the surface, which we don't understand,"},{"time":790000,"text":"as well as about a dozen other areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"Practice makes perfect."},{"time":795000,"text":"How do we know we can do it?"},{"time":797000,"text":"Because we have tested ARES model,"},{"time":801000,"text":"several models in a half a dozen wind tunnels"},{"time":804000,"text":"at the NASA Langley Research Center for eight years,"},{"time":807000,"text":"under Mars conditions."},{"time":809000,"text":"And, of equal importance"},{"time":811000,"text":"is, we test ARES in the Earth's atmosphere,"},{"time":815000,"text":"at 100,000 feet,"},{"time":818000,"text":"which is comparable to the density and pressure"},{"time":821000,"text":"of the atmosphere on Mars where we'll fly."},{"time":824000,"text":"Now, 100,000 feet, if you fly cross-country to Los Angeles,"},{"time":827000,"text":"you fly 37,000 feet."},{"time":829000,"text":"We do our tests at 100,000 feet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"And I want to show you one of our tests."},{"time":835000,"text":"This is a half-scale model."},{"time":837000,"text":"This is a high-altitude helium balloon."},{"time":839000,"text":"This is over Tilamook, Oregon."},{"time":842000,"text":"We put the folded airplane on the balloon --"},{"time":846000,"text":"it took about three hours to get up there --"},{"time":848000,"text":"and then we released it on command"},{"time":850000,"text":"at 103,000 feet,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and we deploy the airplane and everything works perfectly."},{"time":856000,"text":"And we've done"},{"time":858000,"text":"high-altitude and low-altitude tests,"},{"time":860000,"text":"just to perfect this technique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865000,"text":"We're ready to go."},{"time":867000,"text":"I have a scale model here."},{"time":869000,"text":"But we have a full-scale model"},{"time":871000,"text":"in storage at the NASA Langley Research Center."},{"time":874000,"text":"We're ready to go. All we need is a check from NASA headquarters"},{"time":878000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":880000,"text":"to cover the costs."},{"time":882000,"text":"I'm prepared to donate my honorarium for today's talk"},{"time":885000,"text":"for this mission."},{"time":887000,"text":"There's actually no honorarium for anyone for this thing."},{"time":891000,"text":"This is the ARES team;"},{"time":893000,"text":"we have about 150 scientists, engineers;"},{"time":897000,"text":"where we're working with Jet Propulsion Laboratory,"},{"time":899000,"text":"Goddard Space Flight Center,"},{"time":901000,"text":"Ames Research Center and half a dozen major universities"},{"time":904000,"text":"and corporations in developing this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906000,"text":"It's a large effort. It's all at NASA Langley Research Center."},{"time":913000,"text":"And let me conclude by saying"},{"time":916000,"text":"not too far from here,"},{"time":918000,"text":"right down the road in Kittyhawk, North Carolina,"},{"time":921000,"text":"a little more than 100 years ago"},{"time":923000,"text":"history was made"},{"time":925000,"text":"when we had the first powered flight of an airplane on Earth."},{"time":928000,"text":"We are on the verge right now"},{"time":930000,"text":"to make the first flight of an airplane"},{"time":933000,"text":"outside the Earth's atmosphere."},{"time":935000,"text":"We are prepared to fly this on Mars,"},{"time":938000,"text":"rewrite the textbook about Mars."},{"time":940000,"text":"If you're interested in more information,"},{"time":943000,"text":"we have a website that describes this exciting"},{"time":946000,"text":"and intriguing mission, and why we want to do it."},{"time":949000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":951000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}